declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'/---'
Handle *split alias definers* (i.e., functions dynamically defining alias-like
runnables split into two or three low-level aliases, the former typically
accepting one or more passed arguments operated on by the latter).
/---

# ....................{ ALIASES                            }....................
#FIXME: Document me. Note the prefixing newline to separate such evaluation
#from the last argument passed to such alias, as required. Also note that if
#such string local is undefined, eval() reports failure with a suitable error
#message, inducing zeshy to implicitly throw a human-readable exception without
#requiring manual intervation on our part.
alias_global '::'='
    eval "${zeshy_alias_split_expansion__}"'
